# Feature Implementation Guide

## Core Features to Implement

### 1. User Authentication (MVP)

-   Simple 4-digit passcode system
-   No complex security initially (as per requirements)
-   Focus on quick, family-friendly access
-   Plan for future proper auth system

### 2. Adventurer Management

-   Individual user profiles
-   Personal settings page
-   Customizable Pal appearance
-   Gold and progress tracking

### 3. Pal System

-   Low-resolution sprite characters
-   Mood-based visual changes
-   Idle animations
-   Background color customization
-   Gear and equipment system

### 4. Challenge Logging

-   Simple task completion tracking
-   Gold rewards for completed challenges
-   Progress visualization
-   Quick entry system

### 5. Adventure Journal

-   Mood tracking with timestamp
-   Personal notes and updates
-   Visual mood representation
-   History and trends

## Data Models

### Adventurer Interface

```typescript
interface Adventurer {
    id: string
    passcode: string
    backgroundColor: string
    name: string
    battleCry: string
    gold: number
    palId: string
}
```

### Pal Interface

```typescript
interface Pal {
    id: string
    name: string
    adventurerId: string
    mood: MoodType
    gear: Gear[]
}
```

### Challenge Interface

```typescript
interface Challenge {
    id: string
    adventurerId: string
    description: string
    completedAt: Date
    goldReward: number
}
```

## Implementation Patterns

-   Use React Context for shared state
-   Implement proper TypeScript interfaces
-   Plan for Supabase integration
-   Use local storage for MVP, migrate to database later
-   Implement proper error handling and loading states
